    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9616: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Travers</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="68" xml:id="d317fn68">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date to the Minister in Bulgaria as telegram
                        No. 35.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 5, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Your 136, April 3, midnight. The Department wishes you to use your good
                    offices to the end that the Hungarian Government may understand how any support
                    given acts of aggression against Yugoslavia is bound to be regarded in this
                    country. Under existing law <pb facs="0313" n="301" xml:id="pg_301"/> this
                    Government will exert every effort to assist those nations which are defending
                    their independence and integrity against aggression.</p>
                <p>I assume that all information reaching you from the United States (including the
                    Radio Bulletin) is used by you to emphasize the scope of the American Nation’s
                    determination.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
